## Git Handover Workflow

### 1. Receiving Software Architect Handover

When receiving handover from Software Architect:

```bash
# Check handover notes
cat tmp/STORY-XXX-architect-developer-handover.md

# Review design specification
cat docs/technical/STORY-XXX-design.md

# Check implementation tasks
cat project/team/tasks/TASK-XXX-*.md

# Review coding standards
cat docs/technical/CODING_STANDARDS.md
```

### 2. Implementation Planning and Setup

#### Development Environment Setup

```bash
# Set up development branch
git checkout -b feature/STORY-XXX-implementation

# Install dependencies
uv sync --dev

# Run existing tests to ensure clean state
uv run pytest

# Create implementation plan
echo "STORY-XXX Implementation Plan:
- Implementation Approach: [development strategy]
- Code Structure: [file organization]
- Testing Strategy: [testing approach]
- Integration Points: [integration requirements]
- Performance Considerations: [performance requirements]" > docs/technical/STORY-XXX-implementation-plan.md

git add docs/technical/STORY-XXX-implementation-plan.md
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: implementation plan created"
```

#### Task Breakdown and Estimation

```bash
# Break down implementation into smaller tasks
# Estimate effort for each task
# Create detailed task specifications
# Set up task tracking

# Create implementation tasks
git add project/team/tasks/TASK-XXX-impl-*.md
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: create implementation tasks"

# Update task status
git add project/team/tasks/TASK-XXX-*.md
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: update task status to In Progress"
```

### 3. Implementation Execution

#### Test-Driven Development

```bash
# Write failing tests first
# Implement minimal code to pass tests
# Refactor and improve code
# Ensure all tests pass

# Commit test implementation
git add tests/test_STORY-XXX.py
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: add unit tests - [test description]"

# Commit implementation
git add src/rag_pipeline/STORY-XXX.py
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: implement [feature description]"

# Run tests and commit results
uv run pytest tests/test_STORY-XXX.py -v
git add tests/test_STORY-XXX.py
git commit -m "STORY-XXX: Software Developer: tests passing - [test coverage]"
```

#### Code Quality and Standards

```bash
