## Code Implementation Standards

### Function Design Compliance

All functions must follow [function-definitions.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/function-definitions.mdc):

```python
def example_function(
    param1: str,
    param2: int,
    optional_param: bool = False,
) -> dict[str, any]:
    """Brief one-line summary of function purpose.

    More detailed description of what the function does, including
    any important context or business logic.

    Args:
        param1 (str): Description of first parameter
        param2 (int): Description of second parameter
        optional_param (bool, optional): Description of optional parameter.
            Defaults to False.

    Returns:
        dict[str, any]: Description of return value structure

    Raises:
        ValueError: When invalid parameters are provided
        RuntimeError: When operation fails

    Example:
        >>> result = example_function("test", 42, True)
        >>> print(result["status"])
        "success"
    """
    # Implementation here
    pass
```

